# CODEOWNERS — platform-core
#
# Encodes separation-of-duties for the platform's GitOps root and developer chart.
# GitHub requires these owners to review (and, with branch protection "Require
# review from Code Owners" enabled, APPROVE) any PR touching the matched paths —
# including the bot-generated staging bump PR from the capability pipeline. This
# is the release-captain gate that stops an unreviewed capability version from
# reaching staging/production. See
# .github/workflows/capability-pipeline.yaml (bump-staging job) for the rationale.
#
# Owner is a placeholder — replace `@guilhermegreco` with the platform team's
# GitHub team handle (e.g. `@guilhermegreco/platform-team`) once it exists.
#
# HUMAN FOLLOW-UP (cannot be done in this repo alone): enable branch protection
# on `main` with "Require a pull request before merging", "Require review from
# Code Owners", and required status checks. Without protection, CODEOWNERS is
# advisory only and the bot self-merge is not actually blocked.

# All ArgoCD GitOps state (env umbrellas, appsets, apps, ingress, runtimes) —
# the release captain owns what any cluster syncs.
/argocd/            @guilhermegreco
/argocd/**          @guilhermegreco

# Production umbrella is the highest-blast-radius path; called out explicitly so
# it stays owned even if a broader rule is ever relaxed. (Later, more-specific
# entries win in CODEOWNERS, so keep this after the general argocd rule.)
/argocd/production/     @guilhermegreco
/argocd/production/**   @guilhermegreco

# Developer-facing + platform-owned Helm charts (platform-app, tenant).
/charts/            @guilhermegreco
/charts/**          @guilhermegreco

# The governed CI pipeline + pinned tool versions define what every capability
# repo runs; changes here are effectively org-wide.
/.github/           @guilhermegreco
/.github/**         @guilhermegreco
